canonical:
  title: 宿樂安君禪院
  author: 金敦中
  language: lzh
  text: 偶到山邊寺香煙一室開林深唯竹栢境靜絶塵埃俗耳聞僧語愁膓得酒杯蕭然已淸爽况有月華來
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 宿樂安君禪院
  author: 金敦中
  language: lzh
  text: 偶到山邊寺。香煙一室開。林深唯竹栢。境靜絶塵埃。俗耳聞僧語。愁膓得酒杯。蕭然已淸爽。况有月華來。
korean:
  title: 낙안군 선원에서 자며
  author: 김돈중
  language: kor
  text: |-
    우연히 산가 절에 이르니
    향연이 풍겨 나오는 조그만 집
    우거진 숲은 오직 대[竹]와 잣나무뿐
    고요한 경지라 먼지 티끌 전혀 없네
    속된 귀에 중의 이야길 듣는구나
    시름에 겨운 창자가 술잔을 얻었네
    산뜻하게 벌써 맑고 상쾌해지는데
    하물며 저 달이 둥실 떠와 비치는구나
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0120_010_0130&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Lodging at the Chan Monastery of the Lord of Nak-an
  author: Kim Don-jung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I happen upon a temple at the mountain's edge—
    incense smoke drifts through a humble room.
    The deep forest holds only bamboo and pine,
    a realm so still that dust itself has fled.

    My worldly ears hear the monk's discourse,
    while sorrow-heavy in my chest, I find the wine cup.
    Already my spirit grows crisp and clear,
    and then the moon arrives, her radiance falling soft.
  footnotes:
    - The monastery is associated with Nak-an, reflecting the speaker's journey to seek solace in this remote place of spiritual refuge.
    - The progression from hearing Buddhist teaching to accepting wine suggests the speaker's complex path toward peace—through both spiritual and earthly comforts.
